<tool id="fasta_filter_by_length" name="Filter FASTA Sequence by Length">
	<description>user define minimal and maximal length they want</description>
	<command interpreter="python">fasta_filter_by_length.py $input $min_length $max_length $output </command>
	<inputs>
		<param name="input" type="data" format="fasta" label="Fasta file"/>
		<param name="min_length" type="integer" size="15" value="0" label="Minimal length to reurn" />
		<param name="max_length" type="integer" size="15" value="0" label="Maximal length to return" help="no limitation if 0"/> 
	</inputs>
	<outputs>
		<data name="output" format="fasta"/>
	</outputs>
	<tests>
		<test>
			<param name="input" value="454.fna" />
			<param name="min_length" value="10" />
			<param name="max_length" value="0" />
			<output name="output" file="fasta_tool_filter_length_1.out" />
		</test>
	</tests>
	<help>
	
**Example**

Fasta Sequence::

	&gt;seq1
	TCATTTAATGAC
	&gt;seq2
	ATGGC
	&gt;seq3
	TCACATGATGCCG
	&gt;seq4
	ATGGAAGC

Choose minimal length as 10, maximal length as 0 (no limitation), the tool returns::

	&gt;seq1
	TCATTTAATGAC
	&gt;seq3
	TCACATGATGCCG

	</help>
</tool>